<inglise> REGULATION (EC) No 2818/98 OF THE EUROPEAN CENTRAL BANK of 1 December 1998 on the application of minimum reserves (ECB/1998/15) </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA KESKPANGA M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 2818/98 kohustuslike reservide kohaldamise kohta 1. detsember 1998 </eesti>
<inglise> THE GOVERNING COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN CENTRAL BANK, </inglise>
<eesti> (EKP/1998/15) EUROOPA KESKPANGA N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Statute of the European System of Central Banks and of the European Central Bank (hereinafter referred to as 'the Statute') and in particular Article 19.1 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Keskpankade S&uuml;steemi ja Euroopa Keskpanga p&otilde;hikirja (edaspidi "p&otilde;hikiri"), eriti selle artikli 19 l&otilde;iget 1, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EC) No 2531/98 of 23 November 1998 concerning the application of minimum reserves by the European Central Bank (1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 23. novembri 1998. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 2531/98 Euroopa Keskpanga kohaldatavate kohustuslike reservide kohta, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EC) No 2532/98 of 23 November 1998 concerning the powers of the European Central Bank to impose sanctions (2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 23. novembri 1998. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 2532/98 Euroopa Keskpanga volituste kohta rakendada sanktsioone (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 19.1 of the Statute states that, if the European Central Bank (ECB) decides to require credit institutions established in participating Member States to hold minimum reserves, they are to be held on accounts with the ECB and participating national central banks (participating NCBs); whereas it is considered appropriate that such reserves should be held on accounts with participating NCBs; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: p&otilde;hikirja artikli 19 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatakse, et kui Euroopa Keskpank (EKP) otsustab kehtestada osalevates liikmesriikides asutatud krediidiasutuste suhtes kohustusliku reservi n&otilde;ude, tuleb neid reserve hoida EKP ja osalevate riikide keskpankade kontodel; kohustuslike reservide hoidmist osalevate riikide keskpankade kontodel peetakse asjakohaseks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in order to be effective, the instrument of minimum reserves also requires specification regarding the calculation and maintenance of reserve requirements and the reporting and verification rules; </inglise>
<eesti> kohustuslike reservide s&uuml;steemi t&otilde;hususe tagamiseks tuleb kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata ka kohustuslike reservide arvutamise ja hoidmise kord ning aruandlus- ja kontrollieeskirjad; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, for the exclusion of interbank liabilities from the reserve base, any standardised deduction to be applied for liabilities with a maturity of up to two years within the debt securities category and for money market paper should be based on the euro area-wide macro ratio between the stock of relevant instruments issued by credit institutions and held by other credit institutions and by the ECB and participating NCBs, on the one hand, and the total amount outstanding of such instruments issued by credit institutions, on the other, </inglise>
<eesti> pankadevaheliste kohustuste v&auml;ljaj&auml;tmiseks reservibaasist peaksid k&otilde;ik tavap&auml;rased mahaarvamised kuni kaheaastase t&auml;htajaga v&otilde;lakirjadelt ja rahaturuinstrumentidelt p&otilde;hinema &uuml;helt poolt asjaomaste krediidiasutuste v&auml;ljastatud ning muude krediidiasutuste, EKP ja osalevate riikide keskpankade hoitavate asjakohaste vahendite summa ja teiselt poolt krediidiasutuste v&auml;ljastatud selliste vahendite tasumata &uuml;ldsumma suhtarvul kogu eurotsooni kohta, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Definitions </inglise>
<eesti> M&otilde;isted </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Regulation: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses kasutatakse j&auml;rgmisi m&otilde;isteid: </eesti>
<inglise> - 'participating Member State' shall mean an EU Member State which has adopted the single currency in accordance with the Treaty, </inglise>
<eesti> - osalev liikmesriik - EL liikmesriik, kes on koosk&otilde;las asutamislepinguga kasutusele v&otilde;tnud &uuml;hisraha, </eesti>
<inglise> - 'participating national central bank' (participating NCB) shall mean the national central bank of a participating Member State, </inglise>
<eesti> - osaleva riigi keskpank (osalev RKP) - osaleva liikmesriigi keskpank, </eesti>
<inglise> - 'institution' shall mean any entity in a participating Member State which the ECB, under the terms of Article 19.1 of the Statute, may require to hold minimum reserves, </inglise>
<eesti> - asutus - osaleva liikmesriigi iga &otilde;igussubjekt, kellelt EKP v&otilde;ib p&otilde;hikirja artikli 19.1 tingimustel n&otilde;uda kohustusliku reservi hoidmist, </eesti>
<inglise> - 'reserve account' shall mean an institution's account with a participating NCB, the end-of-day balance of which counts towards fulfilment of the institution's reserve requirement, </inglise>
<eesti> - reservikonto - asutuse konto osaleva riigi keskpangas, mille p&auml;eval&otilde;pusaldot v&otilde;etakse arvesse asutuse reservin&otilde;ude t&auml;itmisel, </eesti>
<inglise> - 'reserve requirement' shall mean the requirement for institutions to hold minimum reserves on reserve accounts with participating NCBs, </inglise>
<eesti> - reservin&otilde;ue - asutustele kehtestatud n&otilde;ue hoida osalevate RKPde reservikontodel kohustuslikke reserve, </eesti>
<inglise> - 'reserve ratio' shall mean the percentage specified in Article 4 for any particular item in the reserve base, </inglise>
<eesti> - reservim&auml;&auml;r - reservibaasi iga osa suhtes artiklis 4 t&auml;psustatud protsendim&auml;&auml;r, </eesti>
<inglise> - 'maintenance period' shall mean the period over which compliance with reserve requirements is calculated and for which such minimum reserves must be held on reserve accounts, </inglise>
<eesti> - hoiuaeg - ajavahemik, mil peetakse arvestust reservin&otilde;ude t&auml;itmise kohta ja mille jooksul peab kohustuslikku reservi reservikontol hoidma, </eesti>
<inglise> - 'end-of-day balance' shall mean the balance at the point in time when the finalisation of payment activities and entries related to possible access to the standing facilities of the European System of Central Banks (ESCB) has taken place, </inglise>
<eesti> - p&auml;eval&otilde;pusaldo - saldo hetkel, mil on l&otilde;pule viidud maksed ja kanded, mis on seotud v&otilde;imaliku juurdep&auml;&auml;suga Euroopa Keskpankade S&uuml;steemi (EKPS) p&uuml;sivahenditele, </eesti>
<inglise> - 'NCB business day' shall mean any day on which a particular participating NCB is open for the purpose of conducting ESCB monetary policy operations, </inglise>
<eesti> - RKP pangap&auml;ev - p&auml;ev, mil teatav osalev RKP on avatud EKPSi rahapoliitilisteks toiminguteks, </eesti>
<inglise> - 'resident' shall mean any natural or legal person residing in any of the participating Member States in the sense of Article 1(4) of the Council Regulation (EC) No 2533/98 of 23 November 1998 concerning the collection of statistical information by the European Central Bank (3), </inglise>
<eesti> - resident - f&uuml;&uuml;siline v&otilde;i juriidiline isik, kes elab v&otilde;i asub osalevas liikmesriigis n&otilde;ukogu 23. novembri 1998. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 2533/98 (3) (statistilise teabe kogumise kohta Euroopa Keskpanga poolt) artikli 1 l&otilde;ike 4 t&auml;henduses, </eesti>
<inglise> - 'reorganisation measures' shall mean measures which are intended to preserve or restore the financial situation of an institution and which could affect third parties' pre-existing rights, including measures involving the possibility of the suspension of payments, suspension of enforcement measures or reduction in claims, </inglise>
<eesti> - saneerimismeetmed - meetmed, mis on m&otilde;eldud asutuse varalise seisundi s&auml;ilitamiseks v&otilde;i taastamiseks ja v&otilde;ivad m&otilde;jutada kolmandate isikute olemasolevaid &otilde;igusi, sealhulgas meetmed, mis v&otilde;imaldavad peatada makseid v&otilde;i t&auml;itemeetmeid v&otilde;i v&auml;hendada n&otilde;udeid, </eesti>
<inglise> - 'winding-up proceedings' shall mean collective proceedings concerning an institution which necessarily involve intervention by the judicial authorities or any other competent authority of a participating Member State with the aim of realising assets under the supervision of those authorities, including instances in which the proceedings are terminated by a composition or by another analogous measure. </inglise>
<eesti> - l&otilde;petamismenetlus - asutusega seotud &uuml;hismenetlus, mille korral sekkub osaleva liikmesriigi &otilde;igusasutus v&otilde;i m&otilde;ni muu p&auml;dev asutus, et vara enda j&auml;relevalve all &auml;ra m&uuml;&uuml;a, sealhulgas juhud, mil menetlus l&otilde;petatakse kompromissi v&otilde;i m&otilde;ne analoogse meetme abil. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Institutions subject to reserve requirements </inglise>
<eesti> Reservin&otilde;udega h&otilde;lmatud asutused </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The following categories of institutions shall be subject to reserve requirements: </inglise>
<eesti> Reservin&otilde;uet kohaldatakse j&auml;rgmist liiki asutuste suhtes: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) credit institutions as defined in the first indent of Article 1 of Council Directive 77/780/EEC (4), other than participating NCBs; </inglise>
<eesti> a) n&otilde;ukogu direktiivi 77/780/EM&Uuml; (4) artikli 1 esimeses taandes m&auml;&auml;ratletud krediidiasutused, v&auml;lja arvatud osalevad RKPd; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) branches of credit institutions as defined in the first indent of Article 1 of Council Directive 77/780/EEC, other than participating NCBs; these include branches of credit institutions which have neither their registered nor their head office in a participating Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> b) n&otilde;ukogu direktiivi 77/780/EM&Uuml; artikli 1 esimeses taandes m&auml;&auml;ratletud krediidiasutuste filiaalid, v&auml;lja arvatud osalevate RKPde omad; siia kuuluvad ka selliste krediidiasutuste filiaalid, mille registreeritud asukoht ega peakontor ei asu osalevas liikmesriigis. </eesti>
<inglise> Branches of credit institutions established in participating Member States which are located outside participating Member States are not subject to reserve requirements. </inglise>
<eesti> Reservin&otilde;uet ei kohaldata osalevates liikmesriikides asutatud krediidiasutuste filiaalide suhtes, mis asuvad v&auml;ljaspool osalevaid liikmesriike. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The ECB may exempt the following institutions from reserve requirements on a non-discriminatory basis: </inglise>
<eesti> EKP v&otilde;ib v&otilde;rdse kohtlemise p&otilde;him&otilde;tet j&auml;rgides vabastada reservin&otilde;udest asutused: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) institutions which are subject to winding-up proceedings or reorganisation measures; </inglise>
<eesti> a) mille suhtes on algatatud l&otilde;petamismenetlus v&otilde;i v&otilde;etud saneerimismeetmeid; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) institutions for which the purpose of the ESCB's minimum reserve system would not be met by imposing reserve requirements upon them. </inglise>
<eesti> b) mille suhtes reservin&otilde;ude kehtestamine ei aitaks t&auml;ita EKPSi kohustuslike reservide s&uuml;steemi eesm&auml;rki. </eesti>
<inglise> In reaching a decision on any such exemption, the ECB will take into account one or more of the following criteria: </inglise>
<eesti> Sellise vabastuse otsustamisel v&otilde;tab EKP arvesse &uuml;hte v&otilde;i mitut j&auml;rgmist tingimust: </eesti>
<inglise> (i) the institution is pursuing special-purpose functions; </inglise>
<eesti> i) asutus t&auml;idab eri&uuml;lesandeid; </eesti>
<inglise> (ii) the institution is not exercising active banking functions in competition with other credit institutions; </inglise>
<eesti> ii) asutus ei konkureeri pangandustegevuse alal muude krediidiasutustega; </eesti>
<inglise> (iii) the institution has all its deposits earmarked for purposes related to regional and/or international development assistance. </inglise>
<eesti> iii) k&otilde;ik asutuse hoiused on ette n&auml;htud piirkondlikuks ja/v&otilde;i rahvusvaheliseks arenguabiks. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The ECB will publish a list of institutions subject to reserve requirements. </inglise>
<eesti> EKP avaldab loendi reservin&otilde;udega h&otilde;lmatud asutustest. </eesti>
<inglise> The ECB will also publish a list of institutions exempt from its reserve requirements for reasons other than being subject to reorganisation measures. </inglise>
<eesti> EKP avaldab ka nende asutuste loendi, mis on reservin&otilde;udest vabastatud muudel kui saneerimismeetmetega seotud p&otilde;hjustel. </eesti>
<inglise> Institutions may rely on these lists when deciding whether their liabilities are owed to another institution that is itself subject to reserve requirements. </inglise>
<eesti> Asutused saavad nende loendite p&otilde;hjal kindlaks teha, kas neil on kohustusi m&otilde;ne teise asutuse ees, mille suhtes kohaldatakse reservin&otilde;uet. </eesti>
<inglise> These lists shall not be determinative of whether institutions are subject to reserve requirements in accordance with this Article 2. </inglise>
<eesti> Need loendid ei v&otilde;imalda siiski otsustada, kas asutuste suhtes kohaldatakse reservin&otilde;uet koosk&otilde;las k&auml;esoleva artikliga 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> Reserve base </inglise>
<eesti> Reservibaas </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The reserve base of an institution shall comprise the following liabilities (as defined within the reporting framework for the money and banking statistics of the ECB, which is laid down in Regulation (EC) No 2819/98 of the European Central Bank of 1 December 1998 concerning the consolidated balance sheet of the monetary financial institutions sector (ECB/1998/16)) (5) resulting from the acceptance of funds: </inglise>
<eesti> Asutuse reservibaas koosneb j&auml;rgmistest kohustustest (nagu on m&auml;&auml;ratletud EKP rahandus- ja pangandusstatistika aruandluss&uuml;steemis, mis on s&auml;testatud Euroopa Keskpanga 1. detsembri 1998. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruses (E&Uuml;) nr 2819/98 (5) monetaar-finantsasutuste sektori koondbilansi kohta (EKP/1998/16)), mis tulenevad rahaliste vahendite vastuv&otilde;tmisest: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) deposits; </inglise>
<eesti> a) hoiused; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) debt securities issued; </inglise>
<eesti> b) v&auml;ljastatud v&otilde;lakirjad; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) money market paper. </inglise>
<eesti> c) rahaturuinstrumendid. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The following liabilities shall be excluded from the reserve base: </inglise>
<eesti> Reservibaasist j&auml;etakse v&auml;lja: </eesti>
<inglise> liabilities which are owed to any other institution not listed as being exempt from the ESCB's minimum reserve system according to Article 2(3) and liabilities which are owed to the ECB or to a participating NCB. </inglise>
<eesti> kohustused muude asutuste ees, mida ei ole nimetatud EKPSi kohustuslike reservide s&uuml;steemist artikli 2 l&otilde;ike 3 kohaselt vabastatud asutuste loendis, ja kohustused EKP v&otilde;i osaleva RKP ees. </eesti>
<inglise> For the application of this provision, the institution shall be able to provide evidence to the relevant participating NCB of the actual amount of its liabilities owed to any other institution not listed as being exempt from the ESCB's minimum reserve system and of its liabilities which are owed to the ECB or to a participating NCB in order to exclude them from the reserve base. </inglise>
<eesti> Selle s&auml;tte kohaldamiseks peab asutus suutma asjaomasele osalevale RKP-le t&otilde;endada oma tegelikke kohustusi teiste asutuste ees, mis on EKPSi kohustuslike reservide s&uuml;steemist vabastatud, ja EKP v&otilde;i m&otilde;ne osaleva RKP ees, et need kohustused oleks v&otilde;imalik reservibaasist v&auml;lja arvata. </eesti>
<inglise> If such evidence cannot be presented for debt securities issued with an agreed maturity of up to two years, the institution may apply a standardised deduction to the outstanding amount of its debt securities issued with an agreed maturity of up to two years from the reserve base. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui seda ei ole v&otilde;imalik t&otilde;endada kuni kaheaastase t&auml;htajaga v&auml;ljastatud v&otilde;lakirjade puhul, v&otilde;ib asutus oma k&otilde;nealuste v&otilde;lakirjade tasumata summa reservibaasist standardkorras maha arvata. </eesti>
<inglise> If such evidence cannot be presented for money market paper, the institution may apply a standardised deduction to the outstanding amount of its money market paper liabilities from the reserve base. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui seda ei ole v&otilde;imalik t&otilde;endada rahaturuinstrumentide puhul, v&otilde;ib asutus oma rahaturuinstrumentide tasumata summa reservibaasist standardkorras maha arvata. </eesti>
<inglise> The amount of such standardised deductions will be published by the ECB in the same manner as the publication of the list referred to in Article 2(3). </inglise>
<eesti> EKP avaldab selliste standardsete mahaarvatiste summa samamoodi kui artikli 2 l&otilde;ikes 3 osutatud loendi. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The reserve base in respect of a particular maintenance period shall be calculated by the institution on the basis of the latest data to be reported by the institution to the relevant participating NCB before the start of the relevant maintenance period as defined within the reporting framework for the money and banking statistics of the ECB, which is laid down in Regulation (EC) No 2819/98. </inglise>
<eesti> Asutus arvutab teatava hoiuaja reservibaasi viimaste andmete p&otilde;hjal, mille ta esitab asjaomasele osalevale RKP-le enne asjakohase hoiuaja algust, nagu on m&auml;&auml;ratletud m&auml;&auml;ruses (E&Uuml;) nr 2819/98 s&auml;testatud EKP rahandus- ja pangandusstatistika aruandluss&uuml;steemis. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> Reserve ratios </inglise>
<eesti> Reservim&auml;&auml;rad </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> A reserve ratio of 0 % shall apply to the following liability categories (as defined within the reporting framework for the money and banking statistics of the ECB, which is laid down in Regulation (EC) No 2819/98 </inglise>
<eesti> Reservim&auml;&auml;r on 0% j&auml;rgmist liiki kohustuste puhul (nagu on m&auml;&auml;ratletud m&auml;&auml;ruses (E&Uuml;) nr 2819/98 s&auml;testatud EKP rahandus- ja pangandusstatistika aruandluss&uuml;steemis): </eesti>
<inglise> (a) deposits with agreed maturity over two years; </inglise>
<eesti> a) &uuml;le kaheaastase t&auml;htajaga hoiused; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) deposits redeemable at notice over two years; </inglise>
<eesti> b) &uuml;le kaheaastase &uuml;les&uuml;tlemisajaga hoiused; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) repos; </inglise>
<eesti> c) tagasiostulepingud; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) debt securities issued with an agreed maturity over two years. </inglise>
<eesti> d) &uuml;le kaheaastase t&auml;htajaga v&auml;ljastatud v&otilde;lakirjad. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> A reserve ratio of 2,0 % shall apply to all other liabilities included in the reserve base. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;ikide muude reservibaasi kuuluvate kohustuste puhul on reservim&auml;&auml;r 2,0%. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> Calculation of reserve requirements </inglise>
<eesti> Reservin&otilde;ude arvutamine </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The amount of minimum reserves to be held by each institution in respect of a particular maintenance period shall be calculated by applying the reserve ratios to each relevant item of the reserve base for that period, as defined in Article 4. </inglise>
<eesti> Asutuse kohustusliku reservi summa teataval hoiuajal arvutatakse nii, et k&otilde;nealuse ajavahemiku reservibaasi iga asjakohase osa suhtes kohaldatakse artiklis 4 t&auml;psustatud reservim&auml;&auml;rasid. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> An allowance of EUR 100 000, to be deducted from the amount of the reserve requirement, shall be granted to each institution, subject to the provisions contained in Article 11. </inglise>
<eesti> Iga asutuse reservin&otilde;udest arvatakse maha 100 000 eurot, kui artiklist 11 ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> Reserve holdings </inglise>
<eesti> Reservide hoidmine </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> An institution shall hold its minimum reserves on one or more reserve accounts with the national central bank in each participating Member State in which it has an establishment, in relation to its reserve base in the corresponding Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> Asutus hoiab oma kohustuslikke reserve &uuml;hel v&otilde;i mitmel reservikontol iga sellise osaleva liikmesriigi keskpangas, kus asutusel on m&otilde;ni &uuml;ksus, kusjuures nende suurus tuleneb tema reservibaasist asjaomases liikmesriigis. </eesti>
<inglise> Reserve accounts shall be denominated in euro. </inglise>
<eesti> Reservikontode v&auml;&auml;ring on euro. </eesti>
<inglise> Institutions' settlement accounts with the participating NCBs may be used as reserve accounts. </inglise>
<eesti> Reservikontona v&otilde;ib kasutada asutuse arvelduskontosid osalevas RKPs. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> An institution shall have complied with its reserve requirement if the average end-of-day balance on its reserve accounts over the maintenance period is not less than the amount defined in accordance with Article 5 for that period. </inglise>
<eesti> Asutus on reservin&otilde;ude t&auml;itnud, kui tema reservikontode keskmine p&auml;eval&otilde;pusaldo ei ole hoiuajal v&auml;iksem kui artikli 5 kohaselt selleks ajaks m&auml;&auml;ratud summa. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> If an institution has more than one establishment in a participating Member State, the registered office or head office, if located in that Member State, shall be responsible for ensuring fulfilment of the institution's reserve requirement. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui asutusel on osalevas liikmesriigis rohkem kui &uuml;ks &uuml;ksus, vastutab asutuse reservin&otilde;ude t&auml;itmise eest registreeritud asukoha &uuml;ksus v&otilde;i peakontor, juhul kui see asub k&otilde;nealuses liikmesriigis. </eesti>
<inglise> If the institution has neither a registered office nor a head office in that Member State, it shall designate which branch in that Member State shall be responsible for ensuring fulfilment of the institution's reserve requirement. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui asutusel ei ole k&otilde;nealuses liikmesriigis registreeritud asukohta ega peakontorit, m&auml;&auml;rab ta k&otilde;nealuses liikmesriigis filiaali, kes vastutab asutuse reservin&otilde;ude t&auml;itmise eest. </eesti>
<inglise> All reserve holdings of these establishments count together towards fulfilment of the institution's total reserve requirement in that Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;igi nende &uuml;ksuste hoitavaid reserve v&otilde;etakse arvesse asutuse &uuml;ldise reservin&otilde;ude t&auml;itmisel k&otilde;nealuses liikmesriigis. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> Maintenance period </inglise>
<eesti> Hoiuaeg </eesti>
<inglise> The maintenance period shall be one month, starting on the 24th calendar day of each month and ending on the 23rd calendar day of the following month. </inglise>
<eesti> Hoiuaeg on &uuml;ks kuu ja see algab iga kuu 24. kalendrip&auml;eval ja l&otilde;peb j&auml;rgneva kuu 23. kalendrip&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 8 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 8 </eesti>
<inglise> Remuneration </inglise>
<eesti> Intressiga tasustamine </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Holdings of required reserves are remunerated at the average, taken over the maintenance period, of the ESCB's rate (weighted according to the number of calendar days) for the main refinancing operations according to the following formula: </inglise>
<eesti> Kohustuslike reservide hoidmise pealt makstakse j&auml;rgmise valemi kohaselt intressi, mis v&otilde;rdub EKPSi p&otilde;hiliste refinantseerimistoimingute keskmise (kalendrip&auml;evade arvu j&auml;rgi kaalutud) intressiga hoiuajal: </eesti>
