<eesti> MRi = viimaste p&otilde;hiliste refinantseerimistoimingute intressi piirm&auml;&auml;r kalendrip&auml;eval i. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The remuneration shall be paid on the second NCB business day following the end of the maintenance period over which the remuneration was earned. </inglise>
<eesti> Intressi makstakse RKP teisel pangap&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle hoiuaja l&otilde;ppu, mille eest intressi arvestati. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 9 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 9 </eesti>
<inglise> Responsibility for verification </inglise>
<eesti> Kontrollimiskohustus </eesti>
<inglise> The right to verify the accuracy and quality of the information which institutions provide to demonstrate compliance with the reserve requirement as specified in Article 6 of Regulation (EC) No 2531/98 concerning the application of minimum reserves shall be exercised by the participating NCBs without prejudice to the right of the ECB to exercise this right itself. </inglise>
<eesti> Osalevatel RKPdel on &otilde;igus kontrollida selle teabe &otilde;igsust ja kvaliteeti, mida asutused esitavad reservin&otilde;ude t&auml;itmise t&otilde;endamiseks kohustuslike reservide kohaldamist k&auml;sitleva m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 2531/98 artikli 6 kohaselt, ilma et see piiraks EKP &otilde;igust k&otilde;nealust &otilde;igust ise kasutada. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 10 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 10 </eesti>
<inglise> Indirect holding of minimum reserves through an intermediary </inglise>
<eesti> Kohustuslike reservide hoidmine vahendaja kaudu </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> An institution may apply for permission to hold all its minimum reserves indirectly through an intermediary which is resident in the same Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> Asutus v&otilde;ib taotleda luba k&otilde;igi oma kohustuslike reservide hoidmiseks vahendaja kaudu, kes on sama liikmesriigi resident. </eesti>
<inglise> The intermediary shall be an institution subject to reserve requirements which normally effects part of the administration (e.g. treasury management) of the institution for which it is acting as intermediary, beyond the holding of minimum reserves. </inglise>
<eesti> Vahendaja on reservin&otilde;udega h&otilde;lmatud asutus, kes lisaks kohustuslike reservide hoidmisele &uuml;ldjuhul haldab osaliselt seda asutust (nt rahalisi vahendeid), kelle vahendajana ta tegutseb. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The application for permission shall be addressed to the national central bank of the participating Member State in which the institution making the application is established. </inglise>
<eesti> Loataotlus esitatakse selle osaleva liikmesriigi keskpangale, kus taotlev asutus asub. </eesti>
<inglise> The application shall include a copy of an agreement between the intermediary and the applicant in which both parties express their consent to the arrangement. </inglise>
<eesti> Taotlusele lisatakse &auml;rakiri vahendaja ja taotleja vahelisest lepingust, mis sisaldab m&otilde;lema poole n&otilde;usolekut kokkulepitud korra suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> The agreement shall also specify whether the institution making the application wishes to access ESCB standing facilities and open market operations. </inglise>
<eesti> Peale selle m&auml;&auml;ratakse lepingus kindlaks, kas taotlev asutus soovib juurdep&auml;&auml;su EKPSi p&uuml;sivahenditele ja avaturutehingutele. </eesti>
<inglise> The agreement shall have an agreed period of notice of at least 12 months. </inglise>
<eesti> Lepingu &uuml;les&uuml;tlemisaeg peab olema v&auml;hemalt 12 kuud. </eesti>
<inglise> Upon fulfilment of the above conditions the participating NCB referred to above may grant permission for the period of time for which the aforementioned agreement between the parties is operative, subject to the provisions of paragraph 4 of this Article. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui eespool nimetatud tingimused on t&auml;idetud, v&otilde;ib k&otilde;nealune RKP anda loa pooltevahelise lepingu kehtivuse ajaks, kui k&auml;esoleva artikli l&otilde;ikest 4 ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise> Such permission shall become effective from the start of the first maintenance period following the granting of the permission. </inglise>
<eesti> Luba j&otilde;ustub selle andmisele j&auml;rgneva esimese hoiuaja alguses. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> The intermediary shall maintain these minimum reserve holdings in accordance with the general conditions of the ESCB's minimum reserve system. </inglise>
<eesti> Vahendaja hoiab neid kohustuslikke reserve koosk&otilde;las EKPSi kohustuslike reservide s&uuml;steemi &uuml;ldtingimustega. </eesti>
<inglise> The intermediary shall, in addition to the institutions for which it is acting as intermediary, be responsible for compliance with their reserve requirements. </inglise>
<eesti> Asutuste reservin&otilde;uete t&auml;itmise eest vastutavad nii vahendaja kui ka tema vahendatavad asutused. </eesti>
<inglise> In the event of non-compliance, the ECB may impose any applicable sanctions on the intermediary, on the institution for which it is acting as intermediary, or on both, in accordance with the liability for non-compliance. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui reservin&otilde;udeid ei t&auml;ideta, v&otilde;ib EKP rakendada asjakohaseid sanktsioone vahendaja, vahendaja vahendatava asutuse v&otilde;i m&otilde;lema suhtes, s&otilde;ltuvalt vastutusest t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise eest. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> The ECB or the relevant participating NCB may, at any time, withdraw permission to hold minimum reserves indirectly if an institution which holds its reserves indirectly through an intermediary, or the intermediary itself, fails to comply with its obligations under the ESCB minimum reserve system, if the conditions for the holding of reserves indirectly specified in paragraphs 1 and 2 of this Article are no longer fulfilled or for prudential reasons related to the intermediary. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva artikli l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 s&auml;testatud reservide kaudse hoidmise tingimuste t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmisel v&otilde;i usalduse kaotamisel vahendaja vastu v&otilde;ib EKP v&otilde;i asjaomane osalev RKP kohustuslike reservide kaudse hoidmise loa igal ajal t&uuml;histada, kui asutus, kes hoiab oma reserve vahendaja kaudu, v&otilde;i vahendaja ise ei t&auml;ida oma EKPSi kohustuslike reservide s&uuml;steemist tulenevaid kohustusi. </eesti>
<inglise> If such permission is withdrawn for prudential reasons related to the intermediary, the withdrawal may have immediate effect. </inglise>
<eesti> Usalduse kaotamisel vahendaja vastu v&otilde;ib loa t&uuml;histada kohe. </eesti>
<inglise> Subject to the requirements of paragraph 5 of this Article, any withdrawal for other reasons shall take effect at the end of the current maintenance period. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui k&auml;esoleva artikli l&otilde;ikest 5 ei tulene teisiti, t&uuml;histatakse luba muudel p&otilde;hjustel jooksva hoiuaja l&otilde;pus. </eesti>
<inglise> An institution which holds its reserves through an intermediary, or the intermediary itself, may, at any time, ask for the permission to be withdrawn. </inglise>
<eesti> Asutus, kes hoiab oma reserve vahendaja kaudu, v&otilde;i vahendaja ise v&otilde;ib igal ajal taotleda loa t&uuml;histamist. </eesti>
<inglise> Withdrawal requires prior notification by the relevant participating NCB to become effective. </inglise>
<eesti> Loa t&uuml;histamine eeldab, et asjaomane osalev RKP on sellest eelnevalt teatanud. </eesti>
<inglise> 5. </inglise>
<eesti> 5. </eesti>
<inglise> The institution which holds its minimum reserves through an intermediary and the intermediary itself will be informed of any withdrawal of permission for reasons other than prudential ones at least five working days before the end of the maintenance period within which permission shall cease to be granted. </inglise>
<eesti> Asutusele, kes hoiab kohustuslikke reserve vahendaja kaudu, v&otilde;i vahendajale endale teatatakse muudest p&otilde;hjustest kui usalduse kaotamine tulenevast loa t&uuml;histamisest v&auml;hemalt viis t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva enne selle hoiuaja l&otilde;ppu, mil loa kehtivus l&otilde;peb. </eesti>
<inglise> 6. </inglise>
<eesti> 6. </eesti>
<inglise> Without prejudice to the individual statistical reporting obligations of the institution which holds its minimum reserves through an intermediary, the intermediary shall report the reserve base data in a sufficiently detailed manner to enable the ECB to verify their accuracy and quality, subject to the provisions contained in Article 9, and determine the respective reserve requirements and the reserve holdings data for itself, as well as for each institution for which it acts as intermediary. </inglise>
<eesti> Ilma et see piiraks oma kohustuslikke reserve vahendaja kaudu hoidva asutuse kohustust esitada oma statistilisi andmeid, esitab vahendaja reservibaasi kohta piisavalt &uuml;ksikasjalikud andmed, et EKP saaks artikli 9 kohaselt kontrollida nende &otilde;igsust ja kvaliteeti, ja m&auml;&auml;rab kindlaks reservin&otilde;uded ja hoitavaid reserve k&auml;sitlevad andmed nii enda kui ka iga asutuse kohta, kelle vahendaja ta on. </eesti>
<inglise> These data shall be provided to the participating NCB at which the minimum reserves are held. </inglise>
<eesti> Need andmed esitatakse sellele osalevale RKP-le, kus kohustuslikke reserve hoitakse. </eesti>
<inglise> The intermediary shall provide the aforementioned reserve base data according to the same frequency and timetable as were established within the reporting framework for the money and banking statistics of the ECB, which is laid down in Regulation (EC) No 2819/98. </inglise>
<eesti> Vahendaja esitab eespool nimetatud reservibaasi andmed sama tihti ja samaks t&auml;htajaks, kui m&auml;&auml;ruses (E&Uuml;) nr 2819/98 s&auml;testatud EKP rahandus- ja pangandusstatistika aruandluss&uuml;steem seda n&otilde;uab. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 11 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 11 </eesti>
<inglise> Reserve holding on a consolidated basis </inglise>
<eesti> Reservide konsolideeritud hoidmine </eesti>
<inglise> Institutions allowed to report statistical data as a group on a consolidated basis (as defined within the reporting framework for the money and banking statistics of the ECB, which is laid down in Regulation (EC) No 2819/98) must, subject to the provisions contained in Article 10, hold minimum reserves through one of the institutions in the group which is acting as intermediary exclusively for these institutions. </inglise>
<eesti> Asutused, kellel on lubatud esitada statistilisi andmeid konsolideerituna &uuml;he r&uuml;hmana (nagu on m&auml;&auml;ratletud m&auml;&auml;ruses (E&Uuml;) nr 2819/98 s&auml;testatud EKP rahandus- ja pangandusstatistika aruandluss&uuml;steemis), peavad hoidma kohustuslikke reserve &uuml;he sellisesse r&uuml;hma kuuluva asutuse kaudu, mis on &uuml;ksnes k&otilde;nealuste asutuste vahendaja, kui artiklist 10 ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise> The institution acting as the intermediary for the group may apply to the ECB for exemption from the provisions in paragraph 6 of Article 10. </inglise>
<eesti> R&uuml;hma vahendajana tegutsev asutus v&otilde;ib taotleda EKP-lt erandit artikli 10 l&otilde;ike 6 s&auml;tetest. </eesti>
<inglise> If its application is accepted by the ECB, only the group as a whole shall be entitled to receive the allowance referred to in paragraph 2 of Article 5. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui EKP rahuldab selle taotluse, kohaldatakse artikli 5 l&otilde;ikes 2 osutatud mahaarvamist &uuml;ksnes r&uuml;hma kui terviku suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 12 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 12 </eesti>
<inglise> NCB business days </inglise>
<eesti> RKP pangap&auml;evad </eesti>
<inglise> If one or more branches of a participating NCB are closed on an NCB business day owing to local or regional bank holidays, the relevant participating NCB shall inform the institutions in advance of the arrangements to be made for transactions involving those branches. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks osaleva RKP filiaal on RKP pangap&auml;eval kohaliku v&otilde;i piirkondliku t&auml;htp&auml;eva t&otilde;ttu suletud, annab asjaomane osalev RKP asutustele eelnevalt teada, milline kord kehtib k&otilde;nealuste filiaalidega seotud tehingute suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 13 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 13 </eesti>
<inglise> Transitional provisions </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;leminekus&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The first maintenance period shall start on l January 1999 and end on 23 February 1999. </inglise>
<eesti> Esimene hoiuaeg algab 1. jaanuaril 1999 ja l&otilde;peb 23. veebruaril 1999. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The reserve base of an institution for the first maintenance period shall be defined in relation to elements of its balance sheet as of 1 January 1999, as reported to the participating NCBs within the reporting framework for the money and banking statistics of the ECB, which is laid down in Regulation (EC) No 2819/98. </inglise>
<eesti> Asutuse reservibaas esimesel hoiuajal m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks tema 1. jaanuari 1999. aasta bilansi osade alusel, mis on esitatud osalevatele RKPdele m&auml;&auml;ruses (E&Uuml;) nr 2819/98 s&auml;testatud EKP rahandus- ja pangandusstatistika aruandluss&uuml;steemi kaudu. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 14 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 14 </eesti>
<inglise> Amendments to this Regulation </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse muutmine </eesti>
<inglise> Any amendments to this Regulation shall become effective only with regard to a full maintenance period and shall be announced prior to this period. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse muudatused j&otilde;ustuvad &uuml;ksnes t&auml;ieliku hoiuaja suhtes ja nendest teatatakse enne k&otilde;nealuse aja algust. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 15 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 15 </eesti>
<inglise> Final provision </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;pps&auml;te </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on 1 January 1999. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub 1. jaanuaril 1999. </eesti>
